  <span id="freeText16514824844106949309" style="display:none">My second novel by this author. Once again, I was astounded by the beauty of his writing. This is one of the most masterfully crafted books I have ever read.<br /><br />It is poetically written, risky, and utterly deliberate in its social challenge. The two characters Brink brings to life endear themselves to you, and, in my opinion, will rest in the recesses of your mind for many years.<br /><br />I was shaken by the descriptions of the South African landscape, feeling inspired to explore the raw beauty of a land filled with some a mixed past.<br /><br />Captivating!</span>
