<div id="review_666310117" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/666310117" />
    <a title="Dave Kenyon" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20005663-dave-kenyon"><img alt="Dave Kenyon" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1367581823p2/20005663.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/666310117?book_show_action=true">Jul 12, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dave Kenyon" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dave Kenyon" href="/user/show/20005663-dave-kenyon">Dave Kenyon</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140080148" href="/book/show/734812.An_Instant_in_the_Wind">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer666310117" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12923623238084744419">Brilliant. As expected from Brink. Fascinating story, based on actual events. Enjoyable read, although disturbing at times. He also overdoes the erotic bits; but that&apos;s what you have to expect from Brink. (or maybe I&apos;m being a prude?!) Thought provoking, on many levels. An aspect I really enjoyed was his obvious love for Africa: the indigenous people, landscape, wildlife, scenery etc. I&apos;m fully with him on that count.</span>
  <span id="freeText12923623238084744419" style="display:none">Brilliant. As expected from Brink. Fascinating story, based on actual events. Enjoyable read, although disturbing at times. He also overdoes the erotic bits; but that's what you have to expect from Brink. (or maybe I'm being a prude?!) Thought provoking, on many levels. An aspect I really enjoyed was his obvious love for Africa: the indigenous people, landscape, wildlife, scenery etc. I'm fully with him on that count.</span>
